The bullet engineered with the competitive shooter in mind. Hornady began with a bullet legendary in its accuracy - the Hornady XTP - and redesigned it as the perfect competition projectile. postcontent: Our #PT307918,This listing is for ONE Cylinder Pin. Buyers, however, may take any number of additional pins we may have at the same per-pin price and with no additional shipping charges. Here is the part most often lost from the good little RG14S Revolvers manufactured in Miami by RG Industries during the 1970s and 1980s. Manufacturer is one of our friendly local machine shop here in West Tennessee. Construction is entirely steel, with blued finish. It is designed to fit through the frame and cylinder of an RG14S revolver, and be retained by the cylinder’s internal detent spring, showing in one of our photos right through the center of the cylinder assembly. RG14S Revolvers were manufactured in the late 1970s until the late 1980s, when RG Industries shut down. These will NOT fit an RG14, the earlier models, because the older RG14 had threads on its pin, as the photos show. Any RG14S revolvers will be marked with the S on the left side of their frames, next to the left grip panel, as the photos show. No other RG parts or papers are included. Our pins are machined tighter than the originals. They require a bit more force to insert and remove, but they’re much less likely to fall out from recoil.
